{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-pk-vision","name":"PK vision: agents writing into governed context","kind":"insight","content":"The point of personal knowledge isn't capture — it's that agents can read your context and write back into it under governance. Otherwise you've just rebuilt Notion.","tags":["pk","agents","context"],"createdAt":"2026-04-15T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-07T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-bsbb-on-onboarding","name":"Marcus on onboarding: build smaller, but better","kind":"quote","content":"Marcus: \"Cut step 3 entirely. Make step 2 carry the weight. The onboarding funnel doesn't need more steps — it needs better ones.\"","tags":["onboarding","marcus","quote"],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-jane-customer-priorities","name":"Jane's framing of customer priorities","kind":"reflection","content":"Jane reframed our top-3 customer priorities as: (1) reduce setup time, (2) trust the data is right, (3) play well with existing tools. Sequence matters — we kept hearing #3 first because we were asking #3 first.","tags":["customers","priorities","jane"],"createdAt":"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-q2-okr-draft","name":"Q2 OKRs (draft)","kind":"idea","content":"O1: Ship PK feature to GA. KR1: 3 design partners using daily. KR2: 50 NPS. O2: 30 customer calls. KR1: Synthesize into pattern doc.","tags":["okr","q2"],"createdAt":"2026-05-01T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-01T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-running-form-cue","name":"Running form cue: tall, light, quick","kind":"principle","content":"Three-word reset for running form when fatigue sets in. Tall = posture. Light = footstrike. Quick = cadence (target 180).","tags":["running","cues"],"createdAt":"2026-03-10T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-15T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-spanish-conjunctions","name":"Spanish conjunctions (que / como / cuando)","kind":"idea","content":"que → that. como → as / how. cuando → when. Subjunctive triggered by future-uncertain clauses with cuando.","tags":["spanish","grammar"],"createdAt":"2026-02-15T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-15T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-priya-onboarding-pain","name":"Priya: onboarding pain at Cardinal","kind":"reflection","content":"Cardinal's onboarding pain isn't the steps — it's that step 4 expects data the user doesn't have yet. Same pattern we just heard from two other customers. This might be a category-wide problem.","tags":["customers","priya","onboarding","pattern"],"createdAt":"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-context-graph-thesis","name":"Context graph thesis","kind":"insight","content":"Apps don't need new features; they need a shared substrate. The context graph is the substrate — typed, versioned, query-able by humans and agents alike.","tags":["thesis","graph","architecture"],"createdAt":"2026-03-20T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-02T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-david-fundraise-advice","name":"David: narrative > numbers in fundraise","kind":"quote","content":"David: \"At seed, narrative beats numbers. By A, the numbers either confirm or contradict the narrative. Start with the story you want the numbers to tell.\"","tags":["fundraise","david","quote"],"createdAt":"2026-05-01T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-01T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-elena-rl-paper-summary","name":"Elena's RL paper — summary","kind":"reflection","content":"Elena's draft frames preference learning as a coordination problem rather than a reward-shaping problem. Counterintuitive but cleaner. Need to read sections 4-5 again.","tags":["rl","papers","elena"],"createdAt":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-sara-trip-planning","name":"Trip ideas for December","kind":"journal","content":"Sara wants somewhere warm. Considering: Mexico City + Oaxaca, Lisbon + Porto, Tokyo. Tokyo is most expensive but Sara's never been.","tags":["travel","sara","december"],"createdAt":"2026-04-05T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-05T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-team-offsite-themes","name":"Team offsite — themes","kind":"idea","content":"Offsite themes that surfaced: focus over breadth, ship small but real, fewer meetings, more written. Also: we need a shared definition of 'done'.","tags":["offsite","team","kettle"],"createdAt":"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-pkm-redesign-principles","name":"PKM redesign — atomic, not hierarchical","kind":"principle","content":"Stop nesting notes inside folders inside folders. Each note is one idea, linked horizontally. The graph structure replaces the folder structure.","tags":["pkm","atomic-notes","principle"],"createdAt":"2026-03-25T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-04T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-half-marathon-training-plan","name":"Half-marathon training plan","kind":"idea","content":"16 weeks. Tu/Thu intervals, Sat long run, Sun strength. Build to 18mi long run by week 12. Race week 16.","tags":["running","plan"],"createdAt":"2026-02-05T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-20T00:00:00Z"}}
{"type":"Note","data":{"slug":"note-aaron-design-feedback","name":"Aaron's feedback on the spec","kind":"reflection","content":"Aaron pushed back on the entry point — said the home screen needs to lead with one thing, not three. Probably right. Also: nav cluttered.","tags":["design","aaron","spec"],"createdAt":"2026-05-06T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-06T00:00:00Z"}}

